This paper is about response generation models for dialogue systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper specifically focuses on incorporating external knowledge into the response generation process, which suggests that it may fall under the sub-category of information retrieval (IR). The use of neural networks for response generation also suggests that it may fall under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG). Finally, the paper's use of pointer-generator networks is a common technique in NLP, which suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of neural networks (NE).
